@startuml relay_attack
title Relay Attack — Blocked by UWB Plausibility Checks

actor "Owner\n(phone far away)" as Owner
participant "Relay device A\n(near phone)" as RelayA
participant "Relay device B\n(near car)" as RelayB
participant "Vehicle\nUwbManager" as UWB

Owner -> RelayA : legitimate BLE/UWB (9 m away)
RelayA -> RelayB : forward over long-range link (adds latency)
RelayB -> UWB    : replay UWB ranging (claims NEAR)

note over UWB
  Defence 1: time-of-flight
  relay latency inflates ToF
  ToF > UWB_MAX_TOF_NS  -> reject
end note
UWB --> RelayB : REJECTED (relay_suspected latched)

RelayB -> UWB : retry with faked low ToF + NEAR distance
note over UWB
  Defence 2: distance-rate
  900 cm -> 10 cm in 100 ms
  rate > 500 cm/s  -> reject
  suspicion is LATCHED for the session
end note
UWB --> RelayB : REJECTED (zone forced FAR)

note over UWB : even a valid HMAC cannot reach NEAR -> UNLOCK DENIED
@enduml
